'''Anthony Lenín Valencia Bajaña''' (born 21 July 2003) is an Ecuadorian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for Belgian club [[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Royal Antwerp]] and the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].

==Club career==
Born in the Ecuadorean city of [[Guayaquil]], Valencia began his footballing career with [[Deportivo Azogues]], training with the [[Azogues]]-based side from 2013 until 2014.<ref name=et>{{cite web|url=https://www.eltelegrafo.com.ec/noticias/ecuatorianos-en-el-exterior/1/independiente-europa-anthony-valencia-libertadores|title=Independiente del Valle transfirió a Europa a su figura de la Libertadores Sub20|trans-title=Independiente del Valle transferred the figure from the Libertadores Sub20 to Europe|date=9 June 2022|access-date=28 August 2023|website=eltelegrafo.com.ec|language=es}}</ref> He went on to join [[C.S.D. Independiente del Valle|Independiente del Valle]] in 2017, and represented the club's youth side at the [[U-20 Copa Libertadores]], with his performances earning him a place in [[The Guardian]]'s "Next Generation 2020", highlighting the best young players in world football.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eltelegrafo.com.ec/noticias/futbol-internacional/1/conmebol-destaco-un-golazo-de-anthony-valencia-en-la-libertadores-sub-20|title=Conmebol destacó un 'golazo' de Anthony Valencia en la Libertadores sub-20|trans-title=Conmebol highlighted a 'great goal' by Anthony Valencia in the Libertadores sub-20|date=8 February 2022|accessdate=28 March 2022|website=eltelegrafo.com.ec|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2020/oct/08/next-generation-2020-60-of-the-best-young-talents-in-world-football|title=Next Generation 2020: 60 of the best young talents in world football|date=8 October 2020|accessdate=28 March 2022|work=The Guardian}}</ref>

On 8 June 2022 it was announced that Valencia would join [[Belgian First Division A|Belgian]] club [[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Royal Antwerp]] on a 4 year deal.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://royalantwerpfc.be/nieuws/welkom-anthony-valencia|title=Welkom Anthony Valencia|trans-title=Welcome Anthony Valencia|date=8 June 2022|access-date=8 June 2022|language=nl}}</ref> He notched his first assist for the club in his second appearance for the club; providing the pass for [[Radja Nainggolan]]'s second goal in a 3–1 win over Norwegian opposition [[Lillestrøm SK|Lillestrøm]] in the [[UEFA Europa Conference League]] on 4 August 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.benditofutbol.com/legionarios/anthony-valencia-aprovecha-oportunidades-europa.html|title=Anthony Valencia aprovecha sus oportunidades en Europa|trans-title=Anthony Valencia seizes his opportunities in Europe|first=Paulo|last=Álvarez|date=6 August 2022|access-date=28 August 2023|website=benditofutbol.com|language=es}}</ref> The following month, he scored his first goal for the club; after an attack by Royal Antwerp, the attempted clearance from a Westerlo defender rebounded off forward [[Vincent Janssen]] and fell for Valencia, who headed the ball past goalkeeper [[Sinan Bolat]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.primicias.ec/noticias/jugada/anthony-valencia-royal-antwerp-belgica/|title=Anthony Valencia anota con el Royal Antwerp en Bélgica|trans-title=Anthony Valencia scores for Royal Antwerp in Belgium|date=4 September 2022|access-date=28 August 2023|website=primicias.ec|language=es}}</ref>

